The use and deployment of malicious code protection is determined after careful consideration and after verification that it does not adversely impact the operation of the OT. Malicious code protection tools should be configured to minimize their potential impact on the OT (e.g., employ notification rather than quarantine). Example compensating controls include increase traffic monitoring and auditing. <br>[OT Systems Only: Implementation Statement]<br>

Related Controls: AC-4, AC-19, CM-3, CM-8, IR-4, MA-3, MA-4, PL-9, RA-5, SC-7, SC-23, SC-28, SI-2, SI-4, SI-7, SI-8

